job_title: Business Systems Analyst (Hybrid WFH) - Salt Lake City
job_description: Zions Bancorporation is seeking a Business Systems Analyst (BSA) to join the Channel and Delivery Solutions department of Zions Bancorporation's Chief Technology Office with a knack and curiosity it takes to prevent fraud using modern tools and creative thinking. We are a fast-paced technology team, dedicated to supporting the IT needs of Zions Bancorporation, a regional bank with divisions covering 10 western states. The BSA plays a key role on one of our agile teams, of a cohesive group that maintains and provides solutions for the company's credit systems. We provide technical and application support for multiple operational teams by using dynamic fraud prevention applications, including PayPal, Pindrop, Lexis Nexus, FIS and others. In addition to we use our technical acumen to monitor and maintain our application uptime, pre-emptively provide solutions to mitigate risk, manage vulnerability patches, and machine learning model management. We work closely with the business, risk, and cyber security teams to place/monitor fraud prevention solutions within the Bancorp. Zions Bancorporation is transforming what it means to work for a financial institution. We operate in a fast-paced, information-driven environment, which means we need people who bring diverse experiences, perspectives, and expertise to meet ever-changing demands. Your ability to adapt, learn innovate and collaborate with a dynamic team helps us provide exceptional service to our customers and communities. We are committed to helping our employees grow, develop and advance in their career. Our Workforce of the Future, DEI and Upskilling initiatives allow you to network across the organization, volunteer in our community, and build your technical and soft skills. We believe that investing in your success and well-being is an investment in our customers and our business. Together we are building a culture that values diversity, celebrates growth and creates a space of belonging for all our team members. Our people are what set us apart and make us great. The successful candidate will: Be responsible for various system functions, such as: incident, change, system and project management. Be responsible for troubleshooting (and documenting) website, application, and user access issues. Documenting and escalating incidents, as necessary. Coordinating issue resolution and validating service restoration. Assist in troubleshooting servers, data transmissions, and firewall access issues. Manage various system functions, including change, system and project management. Provide application support for internal customers at our Bancorp affiliates. Ability to perform in a diverse team-based environment. Perform application troubleshooting and make recommendations for improvements. Work with vendors as needed to resolve issues. Be responsible to facilitate new or enhanced change management requests and post change validations. Be responsible for application and infrastructure monitoring, coordinating with Enterprise Technology & Operations and business units on assigning and updating system issues and changes. Perform other duties as assigned. Qualifications: A Bachelor's in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration or other related field and 6 years' experience in business analysis, processes, procedures, project management, etc. or other directly related experience. A combination of education and experience may meet requirements. Advanced knowledge of business systems and applications, incident and change management, project and system management. Requires advanced analytical, organizational, trouble shooting, and problem-solution skills. Ability to elicit, gather and analyze data. Excellent presentation and technical and non-technical communication skills, both verbal and written. Ability to work with vendors. Requires excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to work with both management and staff employees. Must be able to meet deadlines. Working knowledge of various software programs, including word processing, spreadsheets, etc. Preferred Qualifications: Experience with methods of funds transfer including (ACH, wire, electronic) Previous fraud experience Previous experience with data reporting and data reporting tools Experience with apps and applications support with strong knowledge of setup and integration Excellent communication skills Salary Range: Business Systems Analyst IV: $91,400- $101,500 Location: This opportunity will be located in our brand-new Zions Technology Center in Midvale, UT. (We have a hybrid schedule of 3 days in the office and 2 days at home if you are within the Salt Lake City area) The Zions Technology Center is a 400,000-square-foot technology campus in Midvale, Utah. Located on the former Sharon Steel Mill superfund site, the sustainably built campus will be the company's primary technology and operations center. This modern and environmentally friendly technology center will enable Zions to continue to compete for the best technology talent in the state while providing team members with an exceptional work environment with features such as: Electric vehicle charging stations and close proximity to Historic Gardner Village UTA TRAX station. At least 75% of the building is powered by on-site renewable solar energy. Access to outdoor recreation, parks, trails, shareable bikes and locker rooms. Large modern cafe with a healthy and diverse menu. Healthy indoor environment with ample natural light and fresh air. LEED-certified sustainable building that features include the use of low VOC-emitting construction materials. job_title: Platform Delivery Lead - Global Transformation: Plant-To-Produce (Remote Work Opportunity)
job_description: Requisition Number: 60379 Corning is vital to progress - in the industries we help shape and in the world we share. We invent life-changing technologies using materials science. Our scientific and manufacturing expertise, boundless curiosity, and commitment to purposeful invention place us at the center of the way the world interacts, works, learns, and lives. Our sustained investment in research, development, and invention means we're always ready to solve the toughest challenges alongside our customers. Corning's businesses are ever evolving to best serve our customers, industries, and consumers. Today, we accelerate and transform life sciences, mobile consumer electronics, optical communications, display, and automotive markets. We are changing the world with: Trusted products that accelerate drug discovery, development, and delivery to save lives Damage-resistant cover glass to enhance the devices that keep us connected Optical fiber, wireless technologies, and connectivity solutions to carry information and ideas at the speed of life Precision glass for advanced displays to deliver richer experiences Auto glass and ceramics to drive cleaner, safer, and smarter transportation Corning is one of the world's leading innovators in materials science. For more than 160 years, Corning has applied its unparalleled expertise in specialty glass, ceramics, and optical physics to develop products that have created new industries and transformed people's lives. Corning succeeds through sustained investment in R&D, a unique combination of material and process innovation, and close collaboration with customers to solve tough technology challenges. Scope of Position: Support ERP transformation program management strategy planning, program management office execution and follow-ups, and also cross functional program alignment. Partnership with IT solution architect, factory team, GOT change management lead, business power users and value stream lead, as well as related function leads to facilitate ERP transformation deployment projects from initiation through delivery with assigned work stream and functional lead responsibility. Focus on delivery standard platform capability to business users, ensuing adoption from business to understand how to operation with future platform and enable required capability through working close to GT team. Ensure quality platform solution deployment through design, testing, validation and migration protocol and knowledge transfer to operational receiver. Day to Day Responsibilities: Responsible to step into ERP deployment project to work with IT and business counterpart as liaison to trace and track project work items progress. Lead workstream/cross stream communication to ensure risk management assessment are conduct regularly and mitigate plans identified to get program management office attention and support. Lead/participate Process, Security, Data, and Reporting requirement management session, also acting to manage as assigned testing, training, data migration and cut-over lead which partnership with Change Management stream meetings to ensure proper address concerns and mitigate risk impacts. Lead/Participate business early engagement and business readiness phase with business and IT to bringing global template knowledge to gather business requirement, business cases and early identify potential gaps to address through standardization board review and build in for project delivery. Travel Requirements: 25% or less internationally / domestically. Hours of work/work schedule/flextime: Monday - Friday, standard business hours. Required Education: Master's/Bachelor's degrees with business management, industrial engineering, computer science with proper program management training / certifications Required Years and Area of Experience: Min 8 years of SAP functional Plant to Produce experience to work in large-scale project and dynamic environment to lead and deliver global template solution Desire 12 years of SAP functional experience in SAP Production Planning, Material Requirements Planning, Quality Management to work in large-scale project and dynamic environment to lead and deliver global template solution Min 5 years of experience in working with cross functional supply chain modules and leading integration, testing and data migration cycles. 5 years above business, supply chain, functional experience and/or business transformation experience and/or SAP business/functional consultant experience. Required Skills: Hard skills on SAP functional area as consulting skills Soft skills on project management as communication, schedule and scope management and risk managements. Cross functional communication experience Planview / Microsoft Projects or similar project management tools experience Desired Experience / Qualifications / Skills: SAP certification Project Management certification Business analysis or supply chain management related certification Soft Skills: Culture change agent Cross functional communications SAP change agent This position does not support immigration sponsorship. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status or any other legally protected status. Corning Puts YOU First We are committed to supporting your health, financial, career development, and life goals as you grow professionally and personally to achieve your highest potential. All benefits begin as soon as you start your career at Corning. Our monetary peer-to-peer recognition program is tied to our Values and celebrates you and your colleagues' contributions. Health and well-being benefits include medical, dental, vision, mental health/substance use, fitness, and disease management programs. Financial benefits include a 401(k) savings plan with company matching contributions and a 100% company-paid pension benefit that grows steadily throughout your career. Companywide bonus and attractive short- and long-term compensation programs are available based on your role and responsibilities. Professional development programs help you grow and achieve your career goals. We prohibit discrimination on the basis of race, color, gender, age, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, disability, veteran status or any other legally protected status. We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request accommodation. The range for this position is $109,662 to $165,000. Starting pay for the successful applicant is dependent on a variety of job-related factors, including but not limited to geographic location, market demands, experience, training, and education. The benefits available for this position include medical, dental, vision, 401(k) plan, pension plan, life insurance coverage, disability benefits, and PTO. Nearest Major Market: Corning

Job Description: Responsibilities: Developing, managing, and tracking IT projects, from inception to implementation and supporting transition. Forecasting, managing, tracking, and reporting project progress, issues, budget, and scope changes to achieve successful project completion, on-time, and within budget. Managing communications and expectations of clients, sponsors, users, team, contractors and the enterprise while ensuring project adherence to established IT project methodologies and standards, including developing resource plans, risk assessments, project plans, checkpoint reviews, etc. Collects and analyzes data to evaluate PMLC and SDLC operational effectiveness and makes recommendations to solve problems. Follows established modeling and evaluation processes to determine the effectiveness of current operational activities. Partners with the appropriate GTS personnel and users in the maintenance of project management and software development methodology standards and process documentation. Provide user support for Project Management Office tools. Assesses current standards and processes and recommends additional standards and/or modifications to existing processes as the organization evolves. Partners with other GTS personnel to build standard reporting frameworks for tracking and communicating the status of items within the GTS project portfolio. Provide administration support for Project Management Office tools. Trains and coaches individuals and teams on standards, processes and tools. Exhibits Lean-Agile leadership, by reinforcing Agile Core Values and Principles and training teams and individuals on enterprise Agile methodologies. Coaches leaders, teams, Project Managers and Scrum Masters in Lean-Agile leadership, helping to reinforce and embrace Agile Principles and practices. Engages in challenging the old norms of project management and development to improve performance in the areas of quality, predictability, flow and velocity. Responsible for providing task oversight to Level 1 and Level 2 team members. Assigns and delegate tasks as appropriate to ensure timely and successful task completion. Required: Strong communication and interpersonal skills. Detail-oriented, project management skills. Ability to support multiple projects and manage tasks of varying priority. Knowledge of Project Management and Software Development Tools and Processes Familiarity with Agile / Scrum principles. Certificates: Preferred: Project Management Professional (PMP) certification. Preferred: Scaled Agile Framework (SAFE) Scrum Master, Scrum Product Owner, SAFe Program Consultant certification. Experience: 5 years of Project Analyst experience or equivalent. Education: Required: Bachelor's in Information Technology, Business or equivalent.

job_title: Branch Operations Data and Analytics Developer (Telecommute)
job_description: At U.S. Bank, we're on a journey to do our best. Helping the customers and businesses we serve to make better and smarter financial decisions and enabling the communities we support to grow and succeed. We believe it takes all of us to bring our shared ambition to life, and each person is unique in their potential. A career with U.S. Bank gives you a wide, ever-growing range of opportunities to discover what makes you thrive at every stage of your career. Try new things, learn new skills and discover what you excel at-all from Day One. Job Description This individual provides data management support and warehousing development to Branch Operations and Operational Shared Services. They support various reporting/analysis activities as well as business intelligence and dashboard creation for business banking activities. Consumes large amounts of data, analyzes, organizes, and interprets to drive decisions and manage processes amongst the business banking organization. Individual develops in .net languages, creates APIs, and interacts with enterprise data warehouses. Responsible for working on big data/analytics projects that gather and integrate large volumes of data, performs analysis, interprets results and develops actionable insights and recommendations for use across the company. Acquires data from multiple data sources in order to perform analysis. Identifies, analyzes and interprets trends or patterns in complex data in order to provide answers to business questions as well as provide recommendations for action. Interprets data and analyze results using various statistical techniques and tools. Presents data and analysis in a clear and concise manner allowing the audience to quickly understand the results and recommendations so they activate upon them and make data driven decisions. Collaborate with various partners to provide a holistic view of the analysis. Measures and monitors results of applied recommendations and present adjustments. Ensures all data acquisition, sharing and results of applied recommendations are compliant with company standards. Basic Qualifications - Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field such as econometrics, computer science, engineering or applied mathematics, or equivalent work experience - Four to five years of statistical experience Preferred Skills/Experience - Hands on experience working with data bases and proficient in analyzing existing SQL and writing new SQL queries - Database management and ETL/Warehousing proficiency - Working knowledge of Hadoop, R and SAS - Proficiency in analytics data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or other similar tools - Skilled in translating business questions into analytics requirements - Experience packaging analytical output - Ability to take limited direction and self start a project to completion - Ability to upskill peers and fellow team members and train fellow team members on new technologies and infrastructure - Structured documentation protocols and detail oriented operating procedures discipline. - Strong analytic skills with the ability to extract, collect, organize, analyze and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets - Demonstrated project management skills - Effective interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills If there's anything we can do to accommodate a disability during any portion of the application or hiring process, please refer to our disability accommodations for applicants (https://careers.usbank.com/global/en/disability-accommodations-for-applicants) . Learn how the way we work at U.S. Bank (https://assets.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/prod/UBNAGLOBAL/documents/Thewaywework-1666895142717.pdf) drives meaningful relationships with our customers and collaboration across the company. Benefits: Our approach to benefits and total rewards considers our team members' whole selves and what may be needed to thrive in and outside work. That's why our benefits are designed to help you and your family boost your health, protect your financial security and give you peace of mind. Our benefits include the following (some may vary based on role, location or hours): - Healthcare (medical, dental, vision) - Basic term and optional term life insurance - Short-term and long-term disability - Pregnancy disability and parental leave - 401(k) and employer-funded retirement plan - Paid vacation (from two to five weeks depending on salary grade and tenure) - Up to 11 paid holiday opportunities - Adoption assistance - Sick and Safe Leave accruals of one hour for every 30 worked, up to 80 hours per calendar year unless otherwise provided by law EEO is the Law U.S. Bank is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a diverse workforce. We consider all qualified applicants without regard to race, religion, color, sex, national origin, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or veteran status, among other factors. Applicants can learn more about the company's status as an equal opportunity employer by viewing the federal KNOW YOUR RIGHTS (https://eeoc.gov/sites/default/files/2022-10/EEOC\KnowYourRights\screen\reader\10_20.pdf) EEO poster. E-Verify U.S. Bank participates in the U.S. Department of Homeland Security E-Verify program in all facilities located in the United States and certain U.S. territories. The E-Verify program is an Internet-based employment eligibility verification system operated by the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services. The actual range for the role may differ based on the location of the role. In addition to salary, US Bank offers a comprehensive benefits package, including incentive and recognition programs, equity stock purchase 401k contribution and pension (all benefits are subject to eligibility requirements). Pay Range: $87,465.00 - $102,900.00 - $113,190.00 U.S. Bank will consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance. Troubleshooting, root cause analysis, corrective and preventive action. Work closely with Source teams - ETL, HANA and SAP teams for performing RCA for data quality issues. Application Compatibility testing for new browser, java, windows, MS office releases Technical expertise in Spotfire, TIBCO SDK and .Net custom APIs, Spotfire Subscriptions and Automations. Technical expertise in Python, Jenkins and BitBucket need for build and deployment Experience in Spotfire multi node enterprise upgrade, Managing Cloud based spotfire solutions.
